Vice President Mike Pence spoke at the 12th annual summit of Christians United for Israel (CUFI) in Washington, D.C. Pence expressed gratitude for the organization's support and praised President Donald Trump for his commitment to defending faith, restoring freedom, and strengthening the bond between the United States and Israel. Pence highlighted Trump's historic visit to Israel and reiterated the administration's unwavering support for Israel. He also mentioned the appointment of Governor Nikki Haley as Ambassador to the United Nations and the promise to move the American Embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem. Pence emphasized the need for true Palestinian willingness to accept and recognize Israel in any peace negotiations. He also affirmed the administration's commitment to rebuilding the military and standing up to Iran. Pence concluded by expressing his confidence in a prosperous future for Israel and America together.